cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the use of images in state-sponsored information warfare operations, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), multimedia (cs.MM), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of the content and dissemination of these images involves machine learning and data mining techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of social network analysis (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of these operations on popular Web communities, which could also fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR).
